column6: Good vibes, the exercises are really-well explained so I didn't need almost any help! But mentors were always worring about your progress :). We had some free snaks to be comfortable and have fun! I will come back to next events.
column7: Maybe some explanations or introduction about the topic in which we were working.
It'll be cool to include a little talk

column6: I liked that the exercises were organized like a levels in a game.
The place and all the good people in there!
Meeting friends, playing with Node, exploring the SkyScanner office.
working on my own with learnyounode was super easy and I learnt a lot, it's been 3 super productive hours
it was quiet motivational to sit next to the people and just code for the whole purpose of learning. Sometimes it's hard to find the same motivation while you are alone at home.
column7: it wasn't a group experience even so we there were 30 people. how about pair programming? to bring shy lurkers together? but, i guess, it will be not easy to match people of the same skill
